review_blob: A new brewery for me and its off to a great start. This beer has gone straight into my top 5 yorkshire beers!!
The only thing I don't like about this beer is the fact it says limited edition on the label!!
Interesting beer. To be honest I need to try it again to fully make up my mind!!
A nice ruby red ale. Bottled. Not as dark as I would usually choose but still very pleasant.
Had no idea that cropton brewery had changed its name to great Yorkshire, but this beer is just fantastic.
Dark coloured Scottish beer. Smooth tasting with a nice malty finish. Bottled but would love to try this on draft!!
Bottled version tasted. Nice dark beer with smooth taste. Not overly hopped.
St. Austell brewery, sampled this bottled rather than draft. Easy drinking despite being 5% could easily sink a few of these!!
A little hoppy for my liking. Tastes much better if bought on draft, it just doesn't seem the same stuff from a bottle!
A very pleasant black IPA. Brewed for tesco which surprised me. Will be picking up a few more of these!
"Inspired by the American craft beer movement". In other words this beer is hoppy!! Not really a style I love but it does seem to be popular right now.
Would probably make a good session beer. Not memorable enough to go on the favourites list!!
Doesn't take like a strong ale, even the bottled stuff is good. Reminds me of days living and working in that part of Yorkshire.
Pleasant tasting but not an exceptional beer. Always tends to give me a fuzzy head the following day!!
Awesome. That's all that needs to be said! 7.2% and one of the nicest beers ever!
Dark pleasing colour and pleasant aroma but overall a bit lacking in body.
Was surprised by the ginger taste but didn't find it unpleasant. Might consider buying again for a summer BBQ.
I don't usually drink lager but was pleasantly surprised by this!! Seems a bit expensive locally however.
A really nice after dinner beer. Not to one to drink all night but perfectly pleasant for a change.
I'm slightly biased towards this beer as it's from Cornwall, but this is an easy drinking session beer with just the right hints of flavour to not be over powering.
An easy drinking session beer. Not overly hoppy. Often on special offer in Morrisons!
A pretty safe bet, always in draft in one of my local pubs and I'd be sad too see it go.
Pretty good for a lager but generally not my choice of beer. The dark version of this however
One of my personal favourites. Often in supermarket multi buy offers, well worth grabbing a few when it is!
Not particularly outstanding but perfectly drinkable. Wouldn't go looking for it specifically though.
Expected a lot as I'm a big fan of spitfire which I believe comes from the same brewer. Was somewhat disappointed with this though.
Nothing much to say about this really. Probably wouldn't buy again to drink at home, but would be pleasant enough in a bar with limited choices.
beer_name: Shepherd Neame Whitstable Bay Pale Ale (Bottle)

review_blob: A dark and strong beer yet also very easy to drink. If it wasn't 5.6% this could almost be a good session beer!!
Dark mild. Good session beer at 3.7%. Makes a nice change from all the hoppy IPA style beers flooding the market.
Excellent rich stout. Interest after-taste from chipotle. Excellent beer to end the night on.
